Note = {27th International Conference on Interactive Collaborative Learning-ICL,
   Tallinn, ESTONIA, SEP 24-27, 2024},
Abstract = {The study presented in the following pages involved 15 students from the
   Master of Music Therapy program who were asked to compose music using
   the Beatoven.ai website. Participants found the workspace very intuitive
   for creating music. The challenge was to create musical pieces that
   reflect their identity, with the aim of self-discovery and translating a
   description of themselves into music. The activity demonstrated that,
   through artificial intelligence, even those with no experience in music
   composition can express themselves artistically in a therapeutic way.
   The results suggest that the use of AI in music therapy can facilitate
   the process of self-exploration and provide an accessible means of
   artistic expression for all individuals, regardless of their previous
   musical abilities.},
