Abstract = {The emergence of Artificial Intelligence - AI has significantly
   transformed various fields, including music education. This paper
   explores the applications of AI in music education through a systematic
   review of existing literature and case studies. It examines the
   technologies and digital tools available in the music domain,
   emphasizing AI's role in enhancing accessibility and participation for
   students with disabilities and remote learners. Furthermore, the paper
   discusses future trends and ethical concerns, including data privacy,
   bias, and the necessity of human oversight in AI-driven music education.},
