Month = {DEC},
Abstract = {In the coming years, the proliferation of artificial intelligence (AI)
   will lead to changes and challenges to many traditional practices in
   school music and beyond, particularly related to student assessment and
   grading. At the same time, the AI revolution may also facilitate new and
   exciting directions for assessment and differentiation in music
   education. In this article, I offer a range of considerations and
   suggestions for music educators seeking to teach music effectively and
   ethically in the age of AI.},
