Abstract = {Research on generative systems in music has seen considerable attention
   and growth in recent years. A variety of attempts have been made to
   systematically evaluate such systems. We present an interdisciplinary
   review of the common evaluation targets, methodologies, and metrics for
   the evaluation of both system output and model use, covering subjective
   and objective approaches, qualitative and quantitative approaches, as
   well as empirical and computational methods. We examine the benefits and
   limitations of these approaches from a musicological, an engineering,
