Year = {2010},
Volume = {307},
Pages = {153-173},
Abstract = {Music is an exciting area where the computational intelligence has cast
   a deep impact. In this chapter we study a few intelligent systems in the
   domain of music. The vast volume of music available in various formats
   has necessitated the need for their automated classification. Here we
   discuss the system for the identification of genres as well as the
   recognition of artists. These systems have a variety of application in
   playlist generation, music suggestion, music fetching etc. The other
   part of the chapter would focus upon the composition of music. Here also
   we discuss a variety of methods using Genetic Algorithms and Neural
   Networks. The manual assistive design of Genetic Algorithms enables the
   automated composition of music as per human demand. The neural approach
   uses a series prediction phenomenon to compose music when some part of
   it is known. These systems enable good composition techniques which may
   be employed to assist human composers in their task.},
